      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear you, and I want to validate that this feeling of being trapped in a loop of judgment is incredibly draining. It sounds like you are carrying a heavy burden of self-doubt that feels impossible to shake, even when you try to step back. Please remember that your worth is not defined by the opinions of others, and it is okay to not be okay right now. You deserve to feel safe and seen without the constant pressure of performance. If you are feeling overwhelmed, please consider reaching out to a trusted person or a mental health professional who can offer a supportive ear.\n\n***\n\nIt sounds like you are in a very tough spot, feeling like everyone is watching and judging you, which makes it hard to just breathe. It's okay to feel tired and to question how things will ever change. Sometimes, when we feel like we're stuck in a loop, it helps to remember that our internal world is our own, and no one else has the right to dictate how we feel. There are people who care about you and want to help you find a way out of this cycle. Please consider reaching out to a trusted friend, family member, or a mental health professional who can offer support. You are not alone in this struggle",
